fields.description: This field is a description of the image from metadata extraction. It should list people and objects detected in the image. If possible be specific on type of person or item. If there is food, describe the food. Describe the primary colors found in the image. Describe the overall scene and location. Describe any other details that would make it easy to search for this image.

fields.displayName: AI Number of People in Image
fields.description: How many people are in the image? Only list the number like 0, 1, 2 ,3 etc.
List up to 10 descriptive keywords for this image.
Extract the image's dimensions in pixels (format: width x height). If the dimensions cannot be directly extracted, attempt to retrieve them from file metadata.
Image will be one of the following. Portrait, Landscape, or Square
If text is visible, extract it as 'Copy: [extracted text]
format social security number like this XXX-XX-XXXX
Output information as ID expiration date,  ID Number.   Example output: Exp Date: 12/03/2023, ID #123456789

fields.displayName: Employer / authorized representative’s name and title
fields.description: Name on i9 will list last name first.  Output with First name first followed by title

Extract the unique identifier printed on the pay statement (e.g., "Pay Statement #", "Statement No.", "Stub #", or "Check #"); prefer a pay statement/stub number over a check or employee number; exclude account and routing numbers.
Extract the employer's legal name as shown on the pay statement header; ignore payroll provider names (e.g., ADP, Paychex) and bank names.
Extract the employer's mailing address block near the employer name; include street, city, state, and ZIP; ignore employee and bank addresses.
Extract the employee's full name from the pay statement; prefer the labeled employee/payee field; ignore approvers and HR contacts.
Extract the employee's home address block adjacent to the employee name; include street, city, state, and ZIP; ignore employer and bank addresses.
Extract the employee identifier labeled Employee ID/Emp ID/Associate ID; if multiple IDs appear, choose the one explicitly tied to the employee record; do not return SSN or partial SSN.

From the tax/withholding section, select marital status from the allowed list; map common variants (e.g., "M"_Married, "S"_Single, "HOH"_Head of Household; "Exempt" when explicitly marked); if unclear, choose Unknown.
From the withholding section, extract the claimed allowances/exemptions (e.g., "Allowances: 2", "Dependents: 3" or an "Exempt" flag); include the value as written without calculating.
Extract the start date of the pay period; if a range is shown (e.g., 08/01'08/15/2025), return the earlier date; prefer labels like "Period Start"/"From".
Extract the end date of the pay period; if a range is shown, return the later date; prefer labels like "Period End"/"To".
Extract the pay date/check date labeled "Pay Date"/"Check Date"; if both appear, prefer "Pay Date".
For each earnings line, select the earning type from the allowed list; map common abbreviations (REG, OT, DT, HOL, VAC, PTO, SCK, BON, COMM, TIPS, SD, RETRO); if none match, select Other.
For each earnings line, extract the stated rate (e.g., hourly rate, shift differential, per-day); if salaried and no hourly rate is shown, capture the listed rate for that line without converting.
For each earnings line, extract the quantity/hours/units value; prefer the column labeled Hours/Qty/Units; do not infer for salaried lines if not shown.
For each earnings line, extract the current period amount (not YTD) from the Amount/Current column for that line.

For each deduction line, select the type from the allowed list; map common codes (FIT_Federal Income Tax, FICA-SS_Social Security, FICA-MED_Medicare, SIT/LIT_State/Local Tax, SDI_State Disability Insurance, PFL_Paid Family Leave, 401K/ROTH_401(k), HSA/FSA/DC_respective plans); use the closest match.
For each deduction line, extract the current period amount from the Amount/Current column for that line.
For each deduction line, extract the year-to-date amount from the YTD column for that line.
Extract the total YTD gross pay; prefer labels like "YTD Gross", "Total Gross YTD", or summary totals; do not sum manually.
Extract the total YTD deductions; prefer labeled YTD totals in the summary section; do not sum manually.
Extract the total YTD net pay from the YTD summary; ignore per-account net pay distributions.
Extract the current period total earnings/gross (e.g., "Current Gross", "Total Earnings"); ensure it represents the period, not YTD.
Extract the current period total deductions (e.g., "Current Deductions", "Total Deductions"); ensure it represents the period, not YTD.
Extract the current period net pay; prefer the summary line labeled "Net Pay"/"Net Amount"; ignore bank account split amounts and deposit memos.
